data.description: Spacious home in the Gators Grant neighborhood. Current owner isn't a member of the neighborhood pier and waterway access amenities but having that option is an asset for sure! With your personal touch, this home will make a great beach getaway. It has a 2 bedroom septic perk but is actually a 3 bedroom with large Carolina Room off the living area. Two full bathrooms, a laundry room and large kitchen with plenty of cabinets. Outside you'll enjoy the mature oak trees and big yard. A 2 car carport and large storage closet will be the perfect spot for storing fishing and beach gear and parking your boat and cars. The circular driveway provides plenty of parking space and easy access to the home. The beach on the island of Holden Beach is just a few minutes away as well as a public boat ramp and the intracoastal waterway. There are many area golf courses nearby and public parks for all your outdoor hobbies. There is an old well on the property that was previously used for the 4 zone irrigation system. Current owner no longer utilizes that system. The roof was replaced in 2021. Home sits on 4 parcels but the owner is working on having a survey completed to sever approximately 70 X 125 feet for future use leaving 169 X 125 to convey with the home. Most furnishings will convey with the home excluding one bedroom set and the tvs.
